title: Field hockey rankings for Oct. 1, 2015
text:
Junior forward Mayve Clune has 16 goals for No. 2 Moravian Academy (lehighvalleylive.com file photo) By Tom Hinkel | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 01, 2015 7:00 AM View/Post Comments 
FIELD HOCKEY RANKINGS 
Emmaus continues to dominate its competition behind the sensational play of Meredith Sholder , who has 36 goals and 21 assists. Voorhees also continues to play well despite suffering a 2-1 overtime loss to New Jersey state power Madison. Warren Hills has hardly missed a beat. The Blue Streaks knocked off another state power, Bridgewater, last week. Whitehall remains in the fifth spot despite taking its first loss, a 5-0 setback to Emmaus. No. 8 Hackettstown hasn't allowed a goal yet, outscoring its opponents 41-0. Liberty , Bangor , and possibly Pen Argyl , are on the threshold of cracking the Top 10. However, the Hurricanes hurt their chances with a recent 7-2 loss to Easto n. 
Team (last week's ranking), record 
1. Emmaus (1), 10-0 
2. Moravian Academy (2), 11-0 
3. Voorhees (3), 8-2 
4. Warren Hills (4), 7-1 
5. Whitehall (5), 9-1 
7. Southern Lehigh (7), 12-1 
8. Hackettstown (9), 7-0 
9. Parkland (8) 7-3-1 
10. Nazareth (10), 7-5
